      "writtenOn": "2020-11-02T23:36:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ben: I agree, but this CL seems to be doing much more than that. \n\n\u003e can support my theory\n\ndoes this mean you need this temporary? this is a non-trivial amount of complexity: some of it is needed permanently and some is not. I think it is important to distinguish the two.\n\nTo Ben\u0027s point: once the subprocess is done, rdb should explain why it still didn\u0027t exit - that needs to be in the codebase permanently.",
      "parentUuid": "fde73de7_b237cdcb",
      "revId": "685ae912a3f4371c3dfa2fd9ea5292076d78864d",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
